    <div class="twelve wide column">
	
<h2> CALDAM 2015 Special Issue: Call for Papers </h2>
		<p> A special issue of the journal <em> Discrete Applied Mathematics </em> will be published for CALDAM 2015.</p>
		<p>Articles describing original research in the areas of design, analysis and experimental evaluation of algorithms and in discrete applied mathematics are invited for submission to the special issue.  Submitted papers must describe research work that has not been published or accepted   in a refereed journal and is not concurrently under review by a refereed journal or a conference with refereed proceedings.
	       	 Research articles satisfying the above condition may be submitted for review for the special issue, including those that were not submitted to CALDAM 2015.
		</p>
	
    <p><div class="ui sub header">SCOPE</div>
	
  <div class="ui unordered list">
 <div class="item">The range of topics for papers in  the Special Issue includes (but is not limited to) the following.</div>
  
 
  </div>
  </p>
<div class="ui sub header"> Topics Related to Discrete Applied Mathematics </div>
				
				<p>Algebraic Combinatorics | Design Theory | Enumeration | Extremal Combinatorics | Graph Theory | Topological and Analytical Techniques in Combinatorics | Probabilistic Combinatorics | Combinatorial Number Theory | Discrete Geometry | Ramsey Theory</p>
				
				<div class="ui sub header">REVIEW</p>
					All papers submitted to the special issue, including invited papers or selected contributions from published papers in CALDAM 2015, will be reviewed as per the standards of the <em> Discrete Applied Mathematics </em> journal.

				<p><div class="ui sub header">SUBMISSION PROCEDURE</div> </p>
 
				<p> The submission website for the journal is located <a href="http://ees.elsevier.com/dam/default.asp">here</a>. To ensure that all manuscripts are correctly identified for inclusion into the special issue for CALDAM 2015, it is important that authors select SI: CALDAM 2015  when they reach the "Article Type" step in the submission process.  </p>
				<p> In order to reduce the time taken from acceptance to publication, we strongly recommend authors to prepare their article using LaTeX  using the <em>elsarticle.cls</em> class in combination with BibTeX. The elsarticle.cls file and its associated documentation and example files can be downloaded <a href="http://www.ctan.org/pkg/elsarticle">here</a>.

				<p><div class="ui sub header">SUBMISSION DEADLINE</div> </p>
				<p> The submission deadline is July 1, 2015.  Authors are encouraged to submit their papers early so that the review process for the submitted paper can begin early. </p>


            

		</div>
    </div>
